  "text": "We use the Jain's measurement of fairness [CITATION_1] to evaluate the fairness. The experiment result is shown in Figure 4 . RAA and Fair-Method uses different strategies to ensure the fairness of each user. RAA double the utility value between the unallocated users and APs. So the user can get the AP sooner or later, unless the user cancels the request. This strategy ensures the users' fairness of get the wireless network resources. And the experiment proves it has better achieves better fairness than Fair-Method.",
